cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the performance evaluation of protocols in mobile ad hoc networks. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it models human encounter traces. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it proposes a time-variant community mobility model. It may also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as security protocols in mobile networks are often evaluated based on realistic mobility models. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it derives important quantities related to protocol performance.
